text.tspan: Poverty: Share of population living on less than $10 a day, 2021
This data is adjusted for inflation and for differences in the cost of living between countries.
Share living on less than $10 per day
Data source: World Bank PIP; HYDE (2017); Gapminder (2022); UN (2022)
Note: This data is measured in international-$ at 2017 prices. Depending on the country and year, it relates to either disposable income or consumption per capita.
